snippet.textDisplay:
I haven't watched all the video yet, but I can confirm that 16GB of RAM is good for up to around 800 tabs on Chrome. Youtube pages tend to kill it quicker, but hey. Opera and Firefox are good for over 1000 though, I'd say it really starts to funk out around 1300-1500 tabs, depending on what the pages are. They do tend to crash out as you pass 1300, and Firefox in particular will sometimes clear some of the pages but still retain the tab. 500 is about optimal.
Don't ask why I known this....


[Edit: I should confirm that I mean tabs that have been opened and save-closed, then re-opened as an entirety. Obviously as you load the tabs back live it'll bog down.]

I haven't watched all the video yet, but I can confirm that 16GB of RAM is good for up to around 800 tabs on Chrome. Youtube pages tend to kill it quicker, but hey. Opera and Firefox are good for over 1000 though, I'd say it really starts to funk out around 1300-1500 tabs, depending on what the pages are. They do tend to crash out as you pass 1300, and Firefox in particular will sometimes clear some of the pages but still retain the tab. 500 is about optimal.
